JOHANNESBURG - The memorial service for renowned South African musician and producer Robbie Malinga was held at the Grace Bible Church on Friday. The Baby Please and Sobabili hitmaker died on Christmas Day after battling pancreatic cancer following months of bad health, which saw the artist hospitalised a number of times. WATCH: Five artists Robbie Malinga influenced Singer Zahara worked closely with Malinga, and performer at his memorial service.  eNCA